body:
Assigning array members of an array of structs using localparams as index like

```
module array_of_struct_test();

  typedef struct packed {
    bit a;
    int b;
  } t_struct;

  localparam int c_one = 'd1;

  localparam t_struct c_array_of_struct_pass [2] = '{
    'd0:   '{ a: 1, b: 42 },
    'd1:   '{ a: 0, b: 43 }
  };

  localparam t_struct c_array_of_struct_fail [2] = '{
    'd0:   '{ a: 1, b: 42 },
    c_one: '{ a: 0, b: 43 }
  };

endmodule
```

fails on Verilator 4.226 2022-08-31 rev v4.226 with

```
%Error: array_of_struct_localparam.sv:17:5: Assignment pattern key not supported/understood: TEXT
                                          : ... In instance array_of_struct_test
   17 |     c_one: '{ a: 0, b: 43 }
      |     ^~~~~
%Error: Exiting due to 1 error(s)
```
I tracked the error down to V3Width.cpp patVectorMap() but cannot provide a fix.
However, I would expect that the localparam is resolved to a constant.
